        <Parent_String>art genres [300056462], genres in the visual arts [300056444], concepts in the arts and humanities [300056107], Associated Concepts (hierarchy name) [300055126], Associated Concepts Facet [300264086]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genre including physical objects that are meant to be perceived primarily through the sense of sight, were created by the use of skill and imagination, and possess an aesthetic that is valued and of a quality and type that would be collected by art museums or private collectors, including drawings, painting, sculpture, architecture, and decorative arts. Performance art is considered a visual art, but the performing arts and literature are not.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046411/Oxford Companion to Art (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021941/Janson, History of Art (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genre waaronder fysieke objecten vallen die bedoeld zijn om hoofdzakelijk door het oog te worden ervaren, waar vaardigheid en verbeelding te pas zijn gekomen en die van een soort zijn dat door kunstmusea of particuliere verzamelaars wordt verzameld, inclusief tekeningen, schilderingen, sculpturen, architectuur en decoratieve kunstvoorwerpen. Performancekunst valt onder deze categorie, maar uitvoerende kunsten en literatuur niet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gênero que inclui objetos físicos que devem ser percebidos principalmente através do sentido da visão, foram criados pelo uso de habilidade e imaginação e possuem uma estética que é valorizada e de qualidade e tipo que seriam coletados por museus de arte ou colecionadores particulares , incluindo desenhos, pintura, escultura, arquitetura e artes decorativas. A arte performática é considerada uma arte visual, mas as artes cênicas e a literatura não.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
